agger skill so far. <br>
<br>
My plan was to work on either 1hs or 1hb at 13 when I get dual wield and am in full group situations. <br>
<br>
Would you recommend 1hs or 1hb first? If so, what would be a good weapon in the 200-600 price range to complement the tombcarver and help me raise the skill? And what would be a good secondary dagger to use?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Cleg <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uspidor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spidor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/waterchaos.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/12/01 5:19:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidor.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROGUE WEAPONS</span><hr size=1> Whatever the 1hs or 1hb weapon you choose is, make sure it's FAST. A faster weapon means more uses, and a faster skill building ratio. <br>
It also means you'll do more overall damage, even if it's a light damage weapon. Consider; if you do 30 damage when you hit with a weapon that only lets you TRY to hit once every three seconds, your overall damage is less than a weapon that does 15 and lets you try to hit every second... more overall hits means more overall damage. This is the principal that rogue combat is founded upon.<br>
A whip is a nice, fast slashing weapon; some variation of a whip would be a good place to start.<br>
My 2 cents.<br>
 <p>Spidor (Redeemed)

<html><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidor.gif" border="0"></html></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uspidor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spidor</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/waterchaos.gif BORDER=0> at: 7/12/01 5:20:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/udaeroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/11/02 5:57:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROGUE WEAPONS</span><hr size=1> Here are a few weapons I have been looking at recently. I am not lvl 10, but this is just to give you an idea of a few interesting things down the line to help you make your decision. <br>
<br>
Skull Shaped Sacrificial Hammer<br>
MAGIC ITEM  LORE ITEM<br>
Skill: 1HB   Atk Delay: 24<br>
DMG: 6   WT: 6.0   Dmg/Sec: 5.42<br>
STR+2  CHA-15  <br>
Effect: Ritualistic Bloodlust (Unlimited Charges)<br>
Class: ALL<br>
Race: ALL <br>
<br>
The Proc Does:<br>
1: Increase Strength from 10 (L1) to 25 (L30)<br>
2: Increase Absorb Damage (contested amount, but good)<br>
3: Decrease Dexterity by -15 (L1)<br>
<br>
Short Sword of the Ykesha<br>
MAGIC ITEM<br>
Skill: 1HS   Atk Delay: 24<br>
DMG: 8   WT: 4.5   Dmg/Sec: 7.08<br>
Effect: Ykesha - (75 DD after level 36)<br>
Class: BRD PAL RNG ROG SHD WAR <br>
Race: ALL <br>
<br>
Wakizashi of the Frozen Skies<br>
MAGIC ITEM<br>
Skill: 1HS   Atk Delay: 22<br>
DMG: 6   WT: 1.5   Dmg/Sec: 5.91<br>
Effect: Spirit Strike (81 DD)<br>
Class: WAR PAL RNG SHD BRD ROG <br>
Race: ALL <br>
<br>
The thing to remember here is DPS (Damage Per Second). You should not count on a proc to save your life, but having them is with a high DEX is a good way to add a lil kick to your step, so to speak. I currently have 122 Dex and have a proc weapon in both hands ( Crystaline Spider Fang with 12 DD in primary and Short Sword of Ykesha in offhand). My weapons go off for a total of 4-10 procs per mob. While this does not give me cause to run out and solo an even con it does mean my group kills the mob faster, thus less healing is needed, thus less downtime.<br>
<br>
My mistake was deciding at lvl 20 to start 1hs and never starting 1hb (hindsight is 20/20 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ). When I hit 40 1hs had finally maxed for my lvl and both skills with my setup max for lvl within 15 minutes of attaining it (BTW I am 44 now). <br>
<br>
Honestly, I recommend you do both. For pure skill raises with 1hs I recommend:<br>
<br>
Gnoll Hide Lariat<br>
MAGIC ITEM<br>
Skill: 1HS   Atk Delay: 20<br>
DMG: 3   WT: 3.0   Dmg/Sec: 3.50<br>
AC+3  <br>
Effect: Stun (Procs at Level 30)<br>
Class: BRD RNG ROG WAR <br>
Race: ALL <br>
<br>
Forget that you wil more than likely ditch is WAY before it procs. It is just a good, cheap, FAST, weapon which allow for more chances for skill raises. When you get around 20 I would recommend:<br>
<br>
Tentacle Whip<br>
MAGIC ITEM<br>
Skill: 1HS   Atk Delay: 25<br>
DMG: 4   WT: 5.0   Dmg/Sec: 3.60<br>
Effect: Lifetap<br>
Class: BRD PAL RNG ROG SHD WAR <br>
Race: ALL <br>
<br>
Counting on procs is not healthy as I have said before, but this thing has saved my life in the 20's more times than I care to remember.<br>
<br>
As for 1hb.....well Hopefully someone else will cover that. I hope I have been of some help to you. <br>
